metadata.title: Hindsia violacea
metadata.description: Hindsia violacea is a plant in the family Rubiaceae introduced to Britain in 1844, with petals of a fleshy consistency and having a rich velvety-looking surface.

metadata.title: American bog plants
metadata.description: View of a skunk cabbage (Symplocarpus foetidus), a yellow pitcherplant (Sarracenia flava), and a Venus flytrap (Dionaea muscipula) growing on the bank of a pond with hills in the background.

metadata.title: Magnolia hodgsonii
metadata.description: Botanical plate showing a branch of Magnolia hodgsonii bearing flowers and leaves, and bud and fruit on the side.

metadata.title: Magnolia campbellii
metadata.description: View of Magnolia Campbellii flowers and bud on a branch. Campbell's magnolia is a tree in the family Magnoliaceae native to the Himalaya which is cultivated for its spectacular flowers.

metadata.title: Magnolia cathcartii
metadata.description: Botanical plate showing a branch of Magnolia cathcartii with several flowers and buds. Magnolia cathcartii is a tree in the family Magnoliaceae native to Asia.

metadata.title: Flax
metadata.description: Illustration showing a flowering flax plant (Linum usitatissimum), a cultivated species grown for its fibre and its seeds.

metadata.title: Melon Cactus
metadata.description: Illustration showing Melocactus communis, a Jamaican species of the genus melocactus, which contains about thirty-six species.

metadata.title: Common Ivy
metadata.description: Illustration showing Common Ivy, an evergreen climbing plant, growing to 20-30 m high.

metadata.title: Common Lilac
metadata.description: Illustration showing Common Ivy, an evergreen climbing plant, growing to 20-30 m high.

metadata.title: Juniper
metadata.description: Illustration showing Juniper, a coniferous plants in the genus Juniperus of the cypress family Cupressaceae.

metadata.title: Ginkgo biloba
metadata.description: Illustration showing Ginkgo biloba, a Deciduous tree and only extant species of the family Ginkgoaceae.

metadata.title: Quercus lamellosa
metadata.description: Botanical plate showing a branch of Quercus lamellosa with leaves and acorns. Quercus lamellosa is an evergreen oak tree (family Fagaceae) native to Asia.

metadata.title: Meconopsis napaulensis
metadata.description: Botanical plate showing Meconopsis napaulensis flowers, fruit, seeds, and leaves. Meconopsis Napaulensis, also known as Nepal poppy, is a plant of the family Papaveraceae native to Asia.

metadata.title: Aeschynanthus bracteatus
metadata.description: Botanical plate showing a branch of Aeschynanthus bracteatus with flowers and leaves. Aeschynanthus Bracteatus, also known as lipstick vine, is a plant in the family Gesneriaceae native to Asia.

metadata.title: Tulips
metadata.description: The upper parts of tulips of various colors stand in the foreground of an open landscape with a river and a city in the background.

metadata.title: Bellis perennis
metadata.description: Vase arrangement with varieties of daisies in different colors ranging from white to red. Daisies are plants in the family Asteraceae.
